# Grey-headed warbler

| genus = Myiothlypis
| species = griseiceps
| authority = (Sclater, PL & Salvin, 1868)
| synonyms = Basileuterus griseiceps
| range_map = Basileuterus griseiceps map.svg

The grey-headed warbler (Myiothlypis griseiceps) is a species of bird in the family Parulidae.
It is endemic to Venezuela.
Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests.
It is threatened by habitat loss.
